# Codex CLI Command Conversion Template
# TAD v2.1 - Convert Claude Code commands to Codex CLI format

## Source Format
- Location: `.claude/commands/{command-name}.md`
- Format: Markdown

## Target Format
- Location: `~/.codex/prompts/tad_{command-name}.md`
- Format: Markdown (with Codex-specific additions)

## Conversion Rules

### 1. File Naming
- Source: `tad-alex.md`
- Target: `tad_alex.md` (hyphen â†’ underscore, user-level directory)

### 2. Placeholder Conversion
| Claude | Codex |
|--------|-------|
| `$ARGUMENTS` | `$ARGUMENTS` (same) |
| `{args}` | `$ARGUMENTS` |
| `$1, $2` | `$1, $2` (same) |

### 3. Template Structure
```markdown
# TAD {command-name} Command (Codex)

Converted from Claude Code command for Codex CLI compatibility.

---

{original_content}

---

## Codex Execution Notes
- Use $ARGUMENTS for user input
- Skills are in ~/.codex/skills/tad/
- Evidence goes to .tad/evidence/reviews/
```

### 4. Skill References
- Change: "call subagent `code-reviewer`"
- To: "read skill from `~/.codex/skills/tad/code-review/SKILL.md`"

### 5. Path Adjustments
- TAD skills: `~/.codex/skills/tad/{skill-id}/SKILL.md`
- Evidence: `.tad/evidence/reviews/{date}-{skill}-{task}.md`

